# heliolib - SmartHelio's Data Processing Library


`heliolib` is a Python library designed to facilitate data extraction, transformation, sanitation, and metadata extraction for Smarthelio's datasets. The library provides a streamlined way to preprocess and handle data, ensuring the removal of outliers and converting data to a standardized format.

## Installation

To install the `heliolib` library in your project:

Note - It is advisable to use a virtual environment for installing the library.
```
pip install git+https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib.git
```

## Features

- **[Autopilot API Client](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/autopilot_api_client/README.md)**: Sends data to Autopilot via API
- **[Clearsky Modelling](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/clearsky_modelling/README.md)**: Generates Fixed and Single Axis Tracker Clearskycurve (GHI and POA) for any location.
- **[Data Extraction](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/data_extraction_service/README.md)**: Extracts data from various sources and formats.
- **[Data Performance Metrics](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/data_performance_metrics/README.md)**: Provides functions to calculate performance metrics such as PR, Energy yield and Specific Yield.
- **[Data Sanitation](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/data_sanitation_service/README.markdown)**: Removes outliers and sanitizes data based on predefined thresholds.
- **[Data Standardization](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/data_standardization_service/README.md)**: Provides data interpolation kit.
- **[Data Transformation](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/data_transformation_service/README.md)**: Transforms raw data into a multi-index format suitable for further analysis.
- **[Timeseries Data Visualization](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/data_visualization_service/README.md)**: Produces a visual representation of parameters from the inverter and meteo data.
- **[Data Sanitation](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/data_sanitation_service/README.markdown)**: Removes outliers and sanitizes data based on predefined thresholds.
- **[Feature Engineering](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/feature_engineering_service/README.md)**: Generates features such as IAM-adjusted irradiance and expected parameters both at STC and NOCT conditions.
- **[Irradiance Transposition](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/irradiance_transposition_service/README.md)**: Transposes GHI to POA.
- **[Metadata Extraction](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/metadata_extraction_service/README.md)**: Fetches and processes metadata associated with the solar plant.
- **[MongoDB Client](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/mongo_db_client/README.md)**: Allows easy interaction with MongoDB databases.
- **[Rain Data Extraction](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/rain_data_service/README.md)**: Fetches daily rain data from VC and Agrometeo for given periods.
- **[S3 Client](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/s3_client/S3Client.md)**: Allows easy interaction with Amazon S3 bucket
- **[Solar Tools](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/solar_tools/README.md)**: Provides solar-related calculations.
- **[Utils](https://github.com/SmartHelio/heliolib/blob/master/src/heliolib/utils/README.md)**: Provides a diverse range of functions which include adding level to multi-index data frame, api retry session, data frequency calculator and plant extractor.

## Usage

After installing the library, you can use its functionalities as follows:

```python
from heliolib.data_extraction_service import CSVDataExtractor, TimestreamDataExtractor
from heliolib.data_transformation_service import Transformation
from heliolib.data_sanitation_service import DataSanitizer
from heliolib.metadata_extraction_service import MetadataAPI, SystemInfoMetadataAPI

# Example usage code here...
```

For a more comprehensive guide and examples, refer to the provided documentation.


